        "title": "Java 8 Map and Reduce doesnt run",
        "body": "<p>I was using Project Lambdas' .map() method to extract some data from a List object. Before, Jdk 1.8 contained Mapper interface but now, I see that it map method gets Function interface. My method usage below:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code> List&lt;Nut&gt; nutList =new ArrayList&lt;Nut&gt;();\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>I've added some items to nutList and im using below method to extract a fields value by getter.<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>nutList.stream().map(n-&gt;n.getShell())\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>But above n parameter behave like an Object and it doesn't access to original object's method. This usage was normally run with Mapper Functional interface.<\/p>\n",
